  "texts": [
    "The morally relevant features covered by the rule-set will typically be higher-order features, since input features (such as camera pixel inputs) usually do not have direct moral relevance.",
    "For a top-down AMA to function, it therefore either needs to have modules able to extract higher-order features from input features, or it needs to be directly provided with higher-order features by humans.",
    "In the latter case, the AMA could hardly be considered a FMS, since a crucial part of the moral work -recognising which features are potentially morally relevant -will have been taken over by humans.",
    "We therefore focus on the first type.",
    "It is clear that the uncodifiability of moral sensitivity is a direct problem for rule-sets of this form."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}